      "content": "Many legal scholars agree that the existing antitrust framework, designed for the industrial age, is ill-equipped to handle modern digital platforms. The \"walled garden\" structure of search and app ecosystems allows these companies to control the entire user experience, which current laws struggle to address. Therefore, a fundamental shift in regulatory thinking is needed to account for data control and network effects in the digital economy.",
      "source": "target",
